Well Nevada was great. My Dad had a shitty attitude with me most of the time....I got my lip peirced. Um.....I havent been feeling so good lately. I mean Im not sick, I just mean I havent been feeling great about myself. I am thinking about doing stuff to myself a lot. Like burning myself more or taking more pills or cutting again. Ive been thinking about it but I dont do it. I tell myself not to. But the feeling is so overwhelming. Its so much. 

Um...Nothing exciting going on. Nothing ever happens to me...only bad stuff and when something good comes along I fuck it all up. Thats me...one big fuck up. Oh well...I get use to it. 

Its weird. Once you've been called a name...after awhile you get use to it. A name changes who you are. It alters what you see yourself as. When you look at yourself you see what they call you. You see what they want you to see. You see what they make you see. Its very strange how cruel and evil some people can be. Its like people today have no remorse. They dont feel sorry. Its as if nothing happened. People dont care. I mean you try to explain how you feel and how you were treated or whatever but they dont seem to care. They either ignore it or act like nothing is wrong. Take what happened to me when I was in 7th grade. I was picked on a lot. I tried to commit suicide a few times. Ive cried and poured my heart out to my "so-called" friends and they did nothing. They used it agaisnt me to make fun of me. I did drugs once and wouldnt you know it. I told someone who I thought I could trust and she had to tell her ex-boyfriend who was one of the guys who picked on me and he told the other guys and they wouldnt stop. I had to hide from them so they wouldnt find me. I had to hide on the side of my friends house until they left so I could just be with my friends. But when they came back I had to hop a fence and hide once again. I felt like a Jew hiding from the Nazis. I mean God, I didnt do anything. I stood up to one of the guys once. He called me a name and I slapped him in the face, well he got me back. He threw me against the wall and made me go home crying. 2 other guys were there and did NOTHING. All they said was, "You shoudlnt hurt a girl" and the guy who threw me said, "But she isnt a girl". God people can be such assholes. Chris was his name. He said he liked seeing me go home in tears. He fucked me up so bad. He made me feel weak and ugly and stupid and that I didnt belong. I was so insecure and I am still insecure today. Its so sad. I cant even eat in front of people at the thought of what they think about me. I care so mcuh about what people think. I try so hard to be someone Im not. I know my friends can understand who I am but its weird. I cant even be myself around my family.

If they did they would try to help me or something. Instead they just sit back and watch me fuck my life up. One of these days, EVERYONE will be sorry for how they treated me or whatever.
